DAY-5 
METHODS

## What is a Method?
A **method** is a block of code that
- Does **one specific task**
- Can be **reused**
- Makes code **clean and readable**

method-
  static void greet() {
    System.out.println("hello");
  }

calling a method-
 public static void main(String[] args) {
    greet();
  }

Parameterized method - 
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
  static void greet(String name) {
    System.out.println("hello " + name);
  }
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    greet("prem");
  }
}
```

Method with Return Value-

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
  static int add(int a, int b) {
    return a + b;
  }
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    int sum = add(5, 3);
    System.out.println(sum);
  }
}
```

## Important Rules (Must Remember)

1. Method must be **outside `main()`**
2. Method call happens **inside `main()`**
3. Return type must match value returned
4. One method â†’ one responsibility

Task1 -  create a method: static void printHello() and call it from main()

```
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    static void printhello() {
        System.out.println("hello world");
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        printhello();
    }
}
```

Task2 - Create a method: static void printSquare(int n) , Print square of `n`.

```
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    static void printsquare(int n) {
        System.out.println(n * n);
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        printsquare(30);
    }
}
```

Task3 - Create a method: static int findMax(int a, int b) , Return the larger number.

```
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    static int findmax(int a, int b) {
        if (a > b) {
            return a;
        } else {
            return b;
        }
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        int max = findmax(44, 22);
        System.out.println(max);
    }
}
```

Task4 - Create a method : static boolean isPrime(int n) , Return `true` if prime, else `false`.
not attended 

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    static boolean isPrime(int n) {
        if (n <= 1) {
            return false;
        }
        for (int i = 2; i <= n - 1; i++) {
            if (n % i == 0) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(isPrime(7));
        System.out.println(isPrime(10));
    }
}
```

Call method by creating a object of class -

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1
{
    public void printMessage() {
        System.out.println("Hello world");
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        practice1 obj = new practice1();
        obj.printMessage(); 
    }
}
```

call a method within a method - 

```java
import java.util.*;
public class practice1 {
    public static void D() {
        float d = 40.5f;
        System.out.println("In Method D");
    }
    public static void C() {
        double c = 30.5;
        System.out.println("In Method C");
    }
    public static void B() {
        int b = 20;
        C(); // Calling C
        System.out.println("In Method B");
    }
    public static void A() {
        int a = 10;
        B(); // Calling B
        System.out.println("In Method A");
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        A(); // Start with function A
        D(); // Then call D
    }
}
```
